This paper deals with the degrees of freedom (DoF) of a multiantenna cellular network, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the network configurations and channel state information, which are relevant to networking (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SI). The use of multiantenna technology in cellular networks is also related to multimedia (cs.MM) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
